New Lots Ave., at the N.E. corner of Georgia Ave., showing the
Rapelye house. It was demolished in 1929.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, showing only one of the barns of the Rapelye homestead. 2-story brick homes occupy the site since 1929, when these barns were
demolished.

(3)
The same, another view.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(4)
The same, showing another barn. William Rapelye owned them in
1860. In 1873, W. Rapelye Sr. had possession.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
